'''Oncology''' is the medical sub-speciality that deals with the [[study]] and [[treatment]] of [[cancer]]. A [[Medical doctor|doctor]] that practices oncology is called an oncologist. The term originates from the Greek onkos (ονκος), meaning bulk, mass, or tumour; and the suffix -ology, meaning "study of."

